tasks.notes:
WHY: the portal MCP only exposes add/list/complete/reopen, so Claude can't set a due date (or edit any field) on an existing task — e.g. T-0015. The backend ALREADY supports it: patchTaskState() whitelists due/priority/project/title/notes/status and PATCH /api/tasks/:id works. This is purely an MCP-surface addition in app/worker.js. File: poserpilot/brad-portal → app/worker.js (canonical store is brad-claude-context/portal/data/tasks.json per the Worker env).

CHANGE 1 — add to the MCP_TOOLS array (after reopen_todo):
{
  name: "update_todo",
  description: "Update fields of an existing to-do by id — set/clear the due date, or change priority, project, title, notes, or status. Only provided fields change.",
  inputSchema: {
    type: "object",
    properties: {
      id: { type: "string", description: "Task id, e.g. T-0015." },
      due: { type: "string", description: "Due date ISO YYYY-MM-DD; empty string clears it." },
      priority: { type: "string", enum: ["high","med","low"] },
      project: { type: "string" },
      title: { type: "string" },
      notes: { type: "string" },
      status: { type: "string", enum: ["open","in_progress","blocked","done","archived"] }
    },
    required: ["id"]
  }
},

CHANGE 2 — add a branch in runTool() (before the final "Unknown tool" return):
if (name === "update_todo") {
  const id = String(args.id || "");
  if (!id) return { text: "An id is required (e.g. T-0015).", isError: true };
  const patch = {};
  for (const k of ["due","priority","project","title","notes","status"]) {
    if (k in args) patch[k] = (k === "due" && args[k] === "") ? null : args[k];
  }
  const t = await patchTaskState(env, id, patch);
  if (!t) return { text: `No task with id ${id}.`, isError: true };
  return { text: `Updated ${t.id}: "${t.title}"${t.due ? ` (due ${t.due})` : " (no due date)"} [${t.priority}, ${t.project}].` };
}

CHANGE 3 — bump README "Tools exposed:" line to: add_todo, list_todos, complete_todo, reopen_todo, update_todo.

DEPLOY: per app/DEPLOY.md — npx wrangler deploy (from app/). No new secrets/bindings needed.

AFTER DEPLOY: refresh/reconnect the "to do" connector in Claude so the new tool loads (tool list is cached per session).

